This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with segmentation of 3D data from different modalities. It also involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves the use of customized learning procedures, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The use of advanced similarity metrics and the focus on image super-resolution suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The use of multi-modal volumes suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of self-normalization networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
